#. type: Title =
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adjusting color balance\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:7
msgid ""
"![image](images/Tool-Color_Balance-en.png) The **Color Balance** tool allows "
"you to adjust the color balance of your photo around a specified point of "
"the tonal range."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:11
msgid ""
"Additionally, the **Color Balance** tool also allows you to reduce color "
"casts by selecting *neutral gray points*, that is points that you want to be "
"neutral gray in your photo."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:15
msgid ""
"Reducing color casts is most easily done for photos that were taken under "
"mixed lighting conditions and have easily identifiable neutral grays."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "To adjust the color balance or cast of your photo:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:20
msgid "![image](images/Button-Color_Balance.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1.  '
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:25
msgid ""
"Click the color balance tool button in the [tool "
"bar](Tools-Editing.html). (A new color balance tool will appear at the top "
"of the [tool stack](Tool_Stack.html).)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2.  '
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:25
msgid "**To adjust the color balance:**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    1.  '
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:30
msgid ""
"Click anywhere inside the color wheel. (The color balance of your photo will "
"shift towards the color you clicked on.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    2.  '
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:30
msgid ""
"Use the Midpoint slider to set the midpoint of the tonal range of the "
"adjustment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "    **To reduce the color cast:**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    1.  '
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:42
msgid ""
"Click the eyedropper button inside the tool. (The mouse will change to an "
"eyedropper.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    2.  '
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:42
msgid ""
"Click somewhere on your photo that you want to be a neutral gray. (Your "
"photo's colors will shift accordingly. The color swatch and the Red, Green, "
"and Blue values in the tool will also update.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    3.  '
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:42
msgid ""
"If you are satisfied with the color cast reduction, click the eyedropper "
"button again to complete the reduction; otherwise repeat step (b) until you "
"are satisfied."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:49
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Color_Balance.markdown.txt:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** It is often useful to have multiple instances of the color\n"
"balance tool in the [tool stack](Anatomy-Tool_Stack.html) to remove\n"
"color casts from multiple areas of your photo.\n"
msgstr ""

